The paper deals with the task of extracting personal attributes from conversations using deep learning, which is a natural language processing (NLP) problem. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes several neural network models leveraging attention mechanisms and embeddings, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with ranking object values for a given subject-predicate combination, which is a task related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and possibly social networks (cs.SI).
